          xtail - Watch the growth of files.

     SSSSYYYYNNNNTTTTAAAAXXXX
          xxxxttttaaaaiiiillll [-D] file_or_directory ...

     DDDDEEEESSSSCCCCRRRRIIIIPPPPTTTTIIIIOOOONNNN
          _X_t_a_i_l monitors one or more files, and displays all data
          written to the file since command invocation.  When switch-
          ing files in the display, a banner showing the pathname of
          the file is printed.  This command is most useful for moni-
          toring multiple logfiles simultaneously.  If a file is a
          directory, it is monitored for the appearance of new files
          and all new files are monitored in addition to the old ones.
          If a file does not exist, _x_t_a_i_l will wait for it to be
          created.  If the "-D" option is specified, debugging is
          turned on.

          After a period of inactivity on the files being monitored,
          _X_t_a_i_l reduces the frequency of checking for changes, so
          response may sometimes be slower than at other times.

